item.title: WWW Files
item.dc:creator: @Kryptix Kryptix
item.description:
@Kryptix wrote:

[quote=“freaky5000, post:3, topic:434550”]I’m not bad with php and sql intergration, however I personally don’t see the point when I know it’s already done. If it was something nobody else has worked on then I’d probably put the effort into it, which is pretty much the same with everybody using RSCD source they use it because it’s there and already done and they do not have to put put any effort in to creating a brand new source, by investigating RSC all over again and reverse engineering the protocols.

In other words I’m being a lazy bastard.[/quote]
Writing a server base from scratch is much more time consuming than writing some basic web files…

If you can’t be bothered to put any effort into a project then I really don’t see the point of doing it at all; no-one will take you seriously and it’s just a waste of everyone’s time.
